\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ul\b\f0\fs24\lang9 Shopdeploy research\par
\ulnone\fs22 What they do well (must haves for our app)\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0\fs20 Automated Repricing \f1\endash  The most highlighted feature; allows sellers to set price thresholds and automatically adjust listings to stay competitive and win the Buy Box\f0\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\f1 Buy Box Monitoring \endash  Provides instant alerts when a seller loses the Buy Box, enabling quick reaction\f0\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\f1 Order\f2\_\f0 Level Profitability \f1\endash  Calculates net profit per order after all costs, a feature explicitly praised by users\f0\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\f1 Multi\f2\_\f0 Account Management \f1\endash  Lets sellers manage several Takealot seller accounts from a single dashboard, a key need for scaling businesses\f0\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\f1 Mobile Web App \endash  Offers a responsive mobile interface for managing sales and repricing on the go\f0\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\f1 Profit Dashboard: A clean view of Sales - (Takealot Success Fee + Fulfillment Fee + Storage Fee + Cost of Goods) = Net Profit.\f0\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}\f1 Stock Sync: Automatically syncing stock levels between a seller's own website (Shopify/WooCommerce) and Takealot to prevent overselling\f0\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
\b\lang1033 Short comings\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 The Starter plan only allows 100 products and 1 seller account. Sellers with larger inventories or multiple brands must upgrade significantly\lang9\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}The \ldblquote mobile web app\rdblquote  may lack offline functionality, push\f2\_\f0 notification reliability, and performance of a native application\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}No integrations with accounting software (e.g., Xero, QuickBooks), other marketplaces (Amazon SA, Shopify), or logistics providers. No advanced inventory syncing (lead times, returns)\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}No advanced forecasting, competitor\f2\_\f0 price trend analysis, or custom report building. No scraping\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Repricing is rule\f2\_\f0 based (min/max thresholds); lacks machine\f2\_\f0 learning algorithms that factor in demand, seasonality, or competitor behavior.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Does not assist with creating or optimizing listings (e.g., image editing, title/description suggestions).\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Support appears to be email\f2\_\f0 based; no 24/7 live chat or phone support mentioned. We can add voice AI to our app\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Focused solely on Takealot; sellers using other platforms must manage separate tools.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Returns Reconciliation: It doesn't help sellers audit if a returned item was actually received back or if Takealot "lost\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Fee Auditing: It generally calculates estimated fees.[1] It often lacks a "penny-perfect" reconciliation to tell a seller, "Takealot overcharged you R500 in storage fees this month."\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
\b How can we do better\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Remove Arbitrary Limits: Offer plans based on revenue or order volume, not product counts. Allow unlimited products and seller accounts in all but the entry\f2\_\f0 level plan\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Develop a Native Mobile App: Provide full functionality with offline access, real\f2\_\f0 time push notifications, and a smoother user experience.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Expand Integrations: Connect with accounting software, other South African marketplaces (Amazon SA, Bob Shop), and logistics providers (e.g., \cf1\b Aramex, Courier Guy\cf0\b0 ).\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Introduce AI\f2\_\f0 Powered Repricing: Use machine learning to suggest optimal prices based on competitor movements, demand patterns, and profit targets.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Add Listing\f2\_\f0 Creation Tools: Include image\f2\_\f0 background removal, bulk\f2\_\f0 listing creation, and SEO\f2\_\f0 optimized title/description suggestions.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Enhance Analytics: Provide predictive inventory forecasting, competitor\f2\_\f0 price\f2\_\f0 trend charts, and customizable dashboards.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Offer Multi\f2\_\f0 Channel Support: Enable sellers to manage listings, orders, and repricing across Takealot, Amazon SA, and other platforms from one dashboard.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Include Return\f2\_\f0 Management Automation: Help sellers process returns, generate return labels, and track reimbursement status.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Since the API doesn't allow creating products, build a UI form in your app that looks like a modern product builder (drag-and-drop images, easy text inputs). Your backend takes this clean data and generates the perfect Excel CSV for the seller to download and upload to Takealot. This bridges the gap between a nice UI and Takealot's archaic system.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Takealot's API has strict rate limits.[1] Bad tools crash or update slowly when they hit these limits. Creating a "Priority Queue" system.\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li1080\sa200\sl276\slmult1\i High Priority: Items where the seller is close to losing the Buy Box (check these every 5 mins).\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Low Priority: Items with no competition (check these every hour).\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Result: Your repricer will feel faster than ShopDeploy\rquote s without breaking API limits\i0\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 "Lost Stock" Hunter: Build a reconciliation module that compares Units Sent vs. Units Sold vs. Stock on Hand. If the numbers don't add up, flag it so the seller can open a claim. If your tool finds R2000 in lost stock for a seller, it pays for itself instantly.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Whatsapp chat bot that gives you details from your takelot seller account\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf1 NB! \cf0 Automation: Use standard REST APIs for 99% of tasks.[1] Avoid scraping the seller portal with Selenium unless absolutely necessary, as Takealot patches these frequently.\par
\par
\b Pricing suggestions\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Tier 1: Free trail period - Basic repricing, Real-time profitability calculations, Buybox alert.    Tier 2: Gross Merchandise Value (GMV) fee (0.25% of all sales) AI repricing, native mobile app. Tier 3: Tier 2 plus Advanced analytics and custom ERP integration\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Tier 1: Build a reliable Repricer + Profit Dashboard. Price at R249 for early adopters\line Tier 2: Build the CSV solution for product listings and Stock Recon tool. Raise price to R299\line Tier 3: Native Mobile App for push notifications and ERP\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Value based upsell. Offer add\f2\_\f0 ons like advanced forecasting, custom reporting, or multi\f2\_\f0 channel listings for an extra fee\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Offer a "Pay for itself" Guarantee. Market your tool as: "We find lost stock and optimize fees. If our tool doesn't save you its monthly cost in recovered fees or increased Buy Box wins, the month is free."\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
\b Go\f2\_\f0 to\f2\_\f0 Market & Positioning\par

\pard{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf5\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 Target Dissatisfied Shopdeploy Users: Reach out to sellers on forums (e.g., MyBroadband, Hellopeter) who have expressed frustration with limitations or reliability\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Highlight Key Differentiators: Emphasize \ldblquote unlimited products,\rdblquote  \ldblquote AI\f2\_\f0 driven repricing,\rdblquote  \ldblquote native mobile app,\rdblquote  and \ldblquote multi\f2\_\f0 channel support\rdblquote  in all marketing.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Leverage Free Tier: Attract new sellers who are hesitant to commit to a paid tool. Convert them later through superior user experience and value.\par
{\pntext\f5\'B7\tab}Provide Excellent Onboarding & Support: Offer live\f2\_\f0 demo webinars, detailed documentation, and responsive customer support (chat, phone, email).\par

